$ Oracle control file
@ control file

Every Oracle database need a control file.

The controlfile defines some characteristics of the database:
  • database name
  • database creation timestamp
  • names and locations (filesystem paths) of → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/data[data files] and → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/online-redo-log-files[online redo log files]

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/controlfile
